snippet.textDisplay:
I own a Toyota Hilux 1998 model that is getting a complete rebuild I have gone a different path to a lot of people and I have decided to go with a 2.8L bottom end out of a 1994 hilux and a 3.0L / 5.0L head with a 3L denco turbo with a 3 inch exhaust,

It was a bigger build than I thought as i originally was just doing the head and I did and found a hole in the block so that is where this has come together.

But a lot of money spent and my dream getting closer I’m only a few weeks away from having it on the road and on the tracks again!

snippet.textDisplay: Old for sure! There’s something about the shape of the old 4WD’s that are so distinguished. These days BT’s, D Max’s, hilux’s, (tritons 🤢) they all look pretty similar. snippet.textDisplay:
Awesome rig! I also have an old 4x4 its a imported Toyota hilux surf brought it with a blown head and a cracked block.. owner before me was running 30psi in it... I ended up putting a 2001 hilux 1kzt back into it. Its been converted to a mechanical pump. it was an auto till i converted it to a manual out of an old hilux r150f gearbox. It has a 3 inch lift in the rear and 2 inch body lift so i can keep the IFS arms as straight as i can. Yes its not a Solid front i was going to convert it but as it is now it goes anywhere that i point it with a front locker and Shimmed lsd in the rear. lol so im really happy with the IFS at the moment. Probably look at long arm kit in the future. it has 33s on -44 offset true beadlockers. It also has 130lt fuel tank in the rear and 64lt main 194lt all up! it needs airbags in the rear when fully loaded tho lol i also own a stock 2014 LTZ colorado that doesn't get as much attention as the hilux. My surf kinda looks like the little brother of shauno's 80 lol its my pride enjoy thanks for reading if you got this far lol


cheers Ben

I sold that back in July and bought a brand new 2019 Ford Ranger FX4.  The technology in this 4x4 is unbelievable, it is so stable it's almost no fun. snippet.textDisplay: Old Bus all the way Graham coming from a family of Nissan 4wd lovers my old man owned a G60 and then finnaly sold the old girl to buy the 96 td42 Gq that I now own. After the old man seeing the monster 93 Gq Tb42 tuff tourer that I built in the late 90's he fitted a 2" lift under his brand new truck. A few of the boys at 4wd Action would remember my old girl from a few trips between from about 2000 until 2012 anyhow seeing I have taken ownership of the mighty td42 you may ask what the old man upgraded to well you would be happy to know he bought an Mux as he is getting a bit on in years he wanted the comfort of a modern truck but still be able to get out onto properties to hunt but if you ask him what he prefers for all and out offroad performance he would grab the keys to the old Gq any day.

Great video Graham!

We run a 2018 200 series great vehicle perfect for touring in but... I also have a GQ Swb Patrol im building up to be able to carry out maybe the tougher tracks and to not have to worry about beating on the 200.

Shorty is a great example of you don't need the best gear to get you out there and the little truck has probably seen more of this country than most.

So from us I love new 4wds the tech is insane and works well, we prefer them for touring, you can't beat a old school Patrol cheap to fix easy to get parts and alot of fun to drive.

-Brett

snippet.textDisplay: In reply to the question pondered at the end... old or new... OLD for me. Inexpensive to buy and kit out comparitvely. An inexpensive vehicle is cheaper to insure and the company doesn't care what modifications you do to it. Easier to maintain. Way more DIY mechanical repairs and maintenance done by yourself - this can be great learning too when new/young. Parts and accessories readily available and cheap. No cares when merrily drilling into dash for switches and guages and radios and wiring etc.. Also, way less fear worries about panel damage and general breakages - been on too many trips with people with very new/expensive 4WD and when a panel gets a ding... their mood instantly becomes sour and glum and the whole mood of the adventure is ruined.
